'''Gandharvanpattu''' is a [[ritual]] artform in [[North Kerala]].<ref>http://digitalpaper.mathrubhumi.com/c/15989669</ref><ref>http://www.mannarasala.org/dynamic.php?page=mannarasalaFestivals</ref> This ritual is mainly performed by [[Vannan]].<ref>http://www.india9.com/i9show/Kenthran-Pattu-71818.htm</ref> There is five [[theyyam]]s called Rudhirakkali, Varavakkali, Devathe, Mekkkaruvaal, Gandharvan in gandharvanpattu.<ref>http://vtzmp3.com/download/mp3-download/KDNfaI4bkSI.html</ref> This ritual is performed for the blessing of [[bhootam]]. The ritual is performed in the style of [[Kalampattu|kalam pattu]] in [[Kavu]].<ref>http://shodhganga.inflibnet.ac.in/bitstream/10603/173586/7/07_chapter%202.pdf</ref><ref>http://keralaculture.org/kalamezhuthupattu/66</ref> In past times this artform is performed on the houses where pregnant women live<ref>http://www.india9.com/i9show/Kenthran-Pattu-71818.htm</ref> to eliminate different kinds of [[Batha (demon)|badha]](ghost). [[Pulluvaveena]] and [[Pulluvakkudam]] are also used in Gandharvan Pattu.<ref>http://www.scert.kerala.gov.in/images/2015/Plustwo/music.pdf</ref>

In 2017 this artform is performed again in stage.<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-editorialfeatures/deities-dancers-and-drumbeats/article13385395.ece</ref><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KDNfaI4bkSI</ref>

This art is also known as '''Kenthran Pattu<ref>http://www.india9.com/i9show/Kenthran-Pattu-71818.htm</ref>'''

